<div class="container">
    <div style="background:rgba(74,143,231,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(74,143,231,0.2);border-radius:12px;padding:1rem 1.5rem;font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      📊 <strong style="color:#4a8fe7;">Stocks that split historically outperform the S&P 500 by 16% in the following year.</strong> Apple's 4:1 split in 2020 turned 100 shares at $400 into 400 shares at $100 — same value, but more accessible. Calculate your post-split position and adjusted cost basis. <a href="https://gab.ae/news/inflation-eroding-savings-compound-interest-defense-2026" style="color:#4a8fe7;">Understanding market mechanics →</a>
    </div>
    <h1>Stock Split Calculator: Forward &amp; Reverse Splits</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Calculate new share count, adjusted price per share, and cost basis after any stock split or reverse stock split. Total investment value stays the same.</p>
    <div class="updated-badge">Last Updated: March 2026</div>

    <div class="calc-section">
      <h2>Calculate Stock Split</h2>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <div class="calc-inputs">
